  "rationale": "The page argues the brief's arc: reveal \u2192 what shipped \u2192 belief \u2192 ask. The hero adapts the photo-overlay seed into the editorial split-right the style directive calls for (product canvas left, right-anchored serif claim counterweighted by the media), keeping type off the image so no unsanctioned text-on-media occurs. 'What shipped' renders the four agents as ONE repeatable card run (2-up, parallel grammar, each with its real product icon). The beta stat band transfers belief on a light panel \u2014 three credible figures as the hero of each cell \u2014 before a single strong verbatim quote. The close reuses the sanctioned closing-cta-dark deep-teal band, the only mid-run-clearing dark surface, honoring never-dark-mid-page. Accent orange stays on eyebrow, buttons, and links only; all headings are sentence-case serif at weight 500 or below; footer chrome is left to the renderer. Style is locked so every section stays on-grid with no off-grid treatments."
